    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-12-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-12-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="11" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d11">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams.</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1885.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-12-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 10, 1866</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 23d of November, No.
                            1275, is received and approved. In regard to our claims on the ground of
                            violations of neutrality, I think the President’s message well expresses
                            the sense and the feelings of Congress and the people of the United
                            States.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Chales Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
